<h2>Home</h2>
<p>There are multiple electronic communication options. It is very beneficial because it helps businesses and individuals communicate with one another without having to be in person. </p>
<p>There are many different devices you may use to communicate electronically such as a smart phone, computer, laptop or  tablet. All of them have their own features and some may not be able to do the same thing another device can. </p>
<p>Here are a few different ways to communicate electronically:</p>
<ul>
- Text/Message <br>
- Email<br>
- Phone<br>
- Social Media<br>
</ul>

<h2>Phone/texting</h2>
<p>Since the Telephones first patent for invention was given to Alexander Graham Bell in 1876, the effect telephones  and cell phones have had on today's society is unimaginable.</p>
<p>The first handheld phone was produced by Motorola in 1973. Since then handheld cellular devices have become a large part part of majority of peoples daily life. In the Canada alone there are approximately 28,250,000 cell phones in use. </p>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Smiley face" width="300"height="200">

<p>In this day and age Phones are used for many purposes in a teens life such as a program names google classroom in which teachers can create a virtual classroom for their students where they can post assignments and students can submit work and receive marks all from their telephone.</p>
<p>While adults and using their phones to correspond with their work or colleagues through e-mail and text, which is a fast and effective way to share important information and finish projects faster.</p>
<p>Although the wave of new technology and social media platforms have come with an uprise in cyber bullying/harassment. Also the amount of data being trustingly put on your phone is causing hackers to be able to find more personal data easier.</p>
<h2>Email</h2>
<h3>Email (<b>E</b>lecronic <b>Mail</b>)</h3>
<p>Email is a very innovative way to communicate. There are many different companies that offer Email. This form of communication was invented in the 1960's and the name was developed in the 1970's.</p>
<ul>
- Gmail <br>
- Zoho Mail <br>
- Outlook.com <br>
- Mail.com <br>
- Yahoo <br>
</ul>
